-- Gulliver Says Hong Kong Choice for Any HSBC Move, Standard Says
-- B y   J o s h u a   F e l l m a n
-- 2010-09-29T20:19:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-29/gulliver-says-hong-kong-choice-for-any-hsbc-move-standard-says.html
Incoming  HSBC Holdings Plc  Chief
Executive Officer  Stuart Gulliver  said Hong Kong would be the
bank’s top choice as a head office location if it were to leave
London, the Standard reported.  Stephen Green , the bank’s outgoing chairman, said the lender
has no plans to relocate, the Hong Kong-based English-language
newspaper reported today. Both men spoke after the bank held a
board meeting in Shanghai yesterday, the Standard said.   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Fellman at 
 jfellman@bloomberg.net  